    "type": "message",
    "text": "on some level, reminiscent of Facebook's approach of starting at top-tier colleges and only expanding once potential new colleges hit critical mass. except that instead of doing this make sure the social network was densely represented enough to be sticky, Superhuman is doing it for driving their iterative product development. but for sure both examples also have a healthy dose of elitism and FOMO at play.",
