  {
    "client_msg_id": "2dcbdd39-21c7-4dbb-b2fa-6e486093de5d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Watchpoints.  When debugging, I usually need to focus in on one case, but I may not be sure upfront what that case may be.  So it's nice to alternate between grouping, say, all the executions of a line of code together and then focusing on one suspicious one.  For me the frustrating thing is that I'll imagine the manipulation of the possibility space of executions in my head, then be forced to slowly and crudely convert that into tools that my debugger can understand.",
